#. [message]
#: ./scenarios/Outpost.cfg:1260
msgid "The recruiting cost of outlaws is lower than loyalists, and only slightly more expensive than peasants. They are cheap but strong, which is advantageous. But they also have big disadvantages. They easily betray their employers, you in this case. It is very hard to gain their trust. The other disadvantage is their alignment as most battles taken place during the daytime. They usually have two traits like loyalists."
